  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most laws criminalize intentionally disguising the origins of money obtained through illegal activities.",
